explanation: This solution uses a depth-first search (DFS) approach to generate all possible numbers of length n where the difference between every two consecutive digits is k. The DFS function recursively generates all possible numbers by appending digits to the current number. The base case is when n becomes 0, at which point the current number is added to the result vector. The time complexity is O(10^n) because there are 10 possible digits for each position in the number, and the space complexity is also O(10^n) because we need to store all the generated numbers in the result vector.

